physicalLayer

Class SocialActionAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • physicalLayer.Agent
      • physicalLayer.SocialActionAgent

  • public class SocialActionAgent
extends Agent
    An implementation of the Agent abstract class capable of social action, where social action is operationalised as:
    • goal-rational action, where the action taken is considered to be the most likely to achieve a goal;
    • traditional action, where the action taken is comparable to the representative state of the population at the current timestep;
    • random action, where the action taken is completely random.
    A SocialActionAgent is situated in an environment, that has a two-layered neural network architecture for learning and decision-making. Sub-goals are generated by the deliberative layer, and these sub-goals are actioned by the reactive layer which decides on the immediate next steps based on the chosen sub-goals.
    Version:
    v1.2
    Author:
    Chloe M. Barnes

      • evaluate

        public java.lang.Double evaluate(int maxMoves)
        Calculates the fitness based on how many Resources have been collected, how many Stones were placed in the river (and subsequently how much energy was exerted by the cost incurred), and any penalties for loss of life. The number of moves is not currently considered in the fitness measure. This purposefully doesn't "lead" the evolution via fitness.
        Specified by:
        evaluate in class Agent
        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • move

        public Cell[][] move(double[] status,
                     Cell[][] grid)
        Performs actions to be taken in a single move in a single timestep, based on the current state. Decisions are based on the current status (what cell it is on, whether it is carrying a stone, whether a bridge is partially built), where a hill-climbing approach is used to achieve sub-goals (via the reactive layer). If the cell to move to contains a Stone, then it will automatically be picked up. Likewise, if a Stone is being carried and then the cell to move to is Water, the Stone will automatically be dropped and a bridge will be made.
        Specified by:
        move in class Agent
        Parameters:
        status - An array representing the current status: grass, resource, stone, water, carrying status, partial bridge built, where value is 1 if true and 0 otherwise.
        grid - The current state of the environment.
        Returns:
        The updated state of the environment including the new location of the Agent.
        See Also:
        ReactiveLayer, DecisionNetwork
